  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b492ab769d202ee4183275be4bff9429, type: 3}
  m_Name: Husband, Husband.
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FlightPaper.ProjectSorrow.Poems.PoemScriptableObject
  id: 19
  title: Husband, Husband.
  author: Robert Burns
  stanzas:
  - lines:
    - I.
    - Husband, husband, cease your strife,
    - '    Nor longer idly rave, sir;'
    - Tho' I am your wedded wife,
    - '    Yet I am not your slave, sir.'
    - '"One of two must still obey,'
    - '    Nancy, Nancy;'
    - Is it man or woman, say,
    - '    My spouse, Nancy?"'
  - lines:
    - II.
    - If 'tis still the lordly word,
    - '    Service and obedience;'
    - I'll desert my sov'reign lord,
    - '    And so, good bye, allegiance!'
    - '"Sad will I be, so bereft,'
    - '    Nancy, Nancy;'
    - Yet I'll try to make a shift,
    - '    My spouse, Nancy."'
  - lines:
    - III.
    - My poor heart then break it must,
    - '    My last hour I''m near it:'
    - When you lay me in the dust,
    - '    Think, think, how you will bear it.'
    - '"I will hope and trust in heaven,'
    - '    Nancy, Nancy;'
    - Strength to bear it will be given,
    - '    My spouse, Nancy."'
  - lines:
    - IV.
    - Well, sir, from the silent dead,
    - '    Still I''ll try to daunt you;'
    - Ever round your midnight bed
    - '    Horrid sprites shall haunt you.'
    - '"I''ll wed another, like my dear'
    - '    Nancy, Nancy;'
    - Then all hell will fly for fear,
    - '    My spouse, Nancy."'
  rating: 4
